Say it so all these nice
people can hear you.

13:45.254 --> 13:47.622
I'm sorry!

13:47.690 --> 13:48.990
Whoo! All right!

13:49.057 --> 13:51.325
Wow, no one's ever stood
up for me like that before.

13:51.393 --> 13:52.493
No?

13:52.561 --> 13:53.894
Well, it's not easy to beat down

13:53.962 --> 13:55.663
a fool and still look...

13:55.731 --> 13:57.765
<i>* Cute as a button. *</i>

14:04.039 --> 14:07.376
Master wants to take
the Precious from us.

14:07.443 --> 14:08.744
You mean the medal?

14:08.811 --> 14:11.880
He plans to destroy our precious!

14:11.948 --> 14:13.982
Okay, first of all,
say it, don't spray it.

14:14.050 --> 14:15.450
Second, I agree with you.

14:15.518 --> 14:19.088
We must kills Master and
gets the precious back.

14:19.155 --> 14:21.957
Wow, look at you! You are brassy.

14:22.025 --> 14:25.527
We leads them through the
tunnel to the jugenherberger.

14:25.594 --> 14:27.529
She likes to drink the nectar.

14:27.597 --> 14:30.798
When they go in,
they won't comes back out!

14:33.335 --> 14:34.468
Roger, you're alive!

14:34.536 --> 14:35.937
What happened to your hair?

14:36.004 --> 14:38.172
What? Nothing.
It burned off in the crash.

14:38.239 --> 14:39.773
I like it. Do you like it?

14:39.841 --> 14:41.842
No. It looks really bad.

14:41.909 --> 14:43.243
Well, you.

14:43.311 --> 14:45.312
Hey, how crazy was
that plane crash, huh?

14:45.380 --> 14:46.947
Luckily no one died but the pilot.

14:47.015 --> 14:48.315
What happened to you?

14:48.383 --> 14:50.885
Well, landed in a tree,
was impaled on a branch,

14:50.953 --> 14:52.153
pulled it out, turned it
into my walking stick.

14:52.221 --> 14:53.555
Very proud of that.

14:53.622 --> 14:55.791
Lost it-- devastated.
And here we are.

14:55.858 --> 14:59.328
Luckily, I know this mountain
from all my I.O.C. ski trips.

14:59.396 --> 15:01.597
In fact, I know a
shortcut to the top.

15:01.665 --> 15:03.132
Fantastic! That's great, Roger!

15:03.200 --> 15:06.535
They goes up, but they
won't comes back down.

15:06.603 --> 15:08.137
What did you say?

15:08.204 --> 15:10.372
I asked if you wanted
to buy some weed.

15:10.440 --> 15:12.975
I said it in a weird voice
so your dad wouldn't hear.

15:13.042 --> 15:14.309
But now he did.

15:14.376 --> 15:16.144
So, you blew the deal.

15:16.211 --> 15:20.114
It was good weed, Steveses.

15:26.287 --> 15:29.356
It's just through here!

15:29.423 --> 15:30.957
Roger?

15:33.894 --> 15:35.795
Something's not right.

15:35.863 --> 15:37.897
Shh, listen!

15:39.934 --> 15:42.869
It's coming from up there.

15:42.937 --> 15:45.873
He'll never escape her clutches.

15:49.110 --> 15:51.378
Where are we?

15:51.446 --> 15:53.614
The youth hostel, silly!

15:56.317 --> 15:57.818
Yes, we are dancing!

15:57.886 --> 16:00.120
Wonderful!

16:01.322 --> 16:02.589
I am Olga.

16:02.657 --> 16:04.958
Welcome to my jugenherberger.

16:05.026 --> 16:06.960
I will make you drink so much,

16:07.028 --> 16:09.429
you will never want
to leave this place.

16:09.497 --> 16:10.797
No, no, I need my wits.

16:15.003 --> 16:17.838
And now,
Hachenscherflaggenschlager.

16:20.008 --> 16:23.410
The precious is mine, mine!

16:25.780 --> 16:28.448
He... betrayed me.

16:28.516 --> 16:30.017
It's over.

16:30.084 --> 16:31.584
He's won.

16:35.489 --> 16:38.725
Circa 1980 Ronald Reagan!

16:38.792 --> 16:40.126
Don't give up, Stan.

16:40.194 --> 16:42.361
You must take the
medal to the I.O.C.

16:42.429 --> 16:45.197
and destroy it by throwing
it into the Olympic torch.

16:45.265 --> 16:47.266
I won't let you down.

16:47.334 --> 16:49.802
Wow, look at me,
talking to my hero.

16:49.869 --> 16:51.904
This could not possibly
get any better.

16:51.972 --> 16:53.405
Oh, no?

16:53.472 --> 16:56.074
How about sharing a Nathan's
hot dog with the Gipper?

16:59.278 --> 17:01.012
When I wake up,
there'd better not be

17:01.080 --> 17:02.847
a weiner slapping me in the face.

17:05.351 --> 17:06.751
Get up!

17:06.819 --> 17:09.887
The time for beer bongs is now!

17:14.761 --> 17:16.695
You lying, thieving, cheater!

17:16.762 --> 17:18.130
You're going to get
what you deserve!

17:18.198 --> 17:20.133
Where do they keep the
British tourist girls?

17:23.738 --> 17:25.839
Look, girls, a present!

17:31.179 --> 17:33.080
No!

17:33.147 --> 17:35.883
They're so horny-y-y-y!

17:41.423 --> 17:43.190
So, we're at the restaurant,

17:43.258 --> 17:44.992
and Ian plucks a
hair out of my head

17:45.060 --> 17:47.395
and puts it in the spaghetti
to try to get us a free meal.

17:47.463 --> 17:48.663
You know what the problem is?

17:48.731 --> 17:50.065
You dating a boy.

17:50.132 --> 17:54.136
What you need to be doing
is dating a grown-ass man.

17:54.204 --> 17:56.939
Well, it's late.
I better head home.

17:57.007 --> 17:58.141
Good night, Hayley.

17:58.208 --> 17:59.342
Good night, Reggie.

17:59.410 --> 18:01.611
I had a great time tonight.

18:03.180 --> 18:05.314
Whoa, girl,
that's the cognac talking.

18:05.382 --> 18:06.982
I'm all up in your head right now.

18:07.050 --> 18:08.451
You're a little bit excited,

18:08.518 --> 18:09.985
you saw Reggie get a
little loose today.

18:10.053 --> 18:11.286
I know what I'm doing.

18:11.354 --> 18:12.721
Hayley, I'm seeing someone.

18:12.789 --> 18:14.723
Oh, you-you never mentioned that.

18:14.791 --> 18:16.058
I didn't think it was relevant.

18:16.125 --> 18:17.692
We were hanging out as friends.

18:17.760 --> 18:20.028
Look, do I know if it's going
to work out with my lady friend?

18:20.095 --> 18:21.362
No, I don't.

18:21.429 --> 18:23.330
But I have to respect Rhonda.

18:23.398 --> 18:25.132
If I didn't, I'd be just like

18:25.200 --> 18:27.368
those boys you run around
with down at the school yard.

18:27.435 --> 18:29.404
Wow, that's really honorable.

18:29.471 --> 18:32.074
She's a lucky lady.

18:32.141 --> 18:33.942
But I want you to know two things.

18:34.010 --> 18:36.445
I sleep with my door unlocked,
and this just happened.

18:41.586 --> 18:44.220
Whoo! She got the
drop on old Reggie.

18:44.288 --> 18:46.222
Caught those full in the face.

18:46.290 --> 18:48.424
Those were guns, Reggie be dead.

18:55.231 --> 18:56.798
There it is!

19:07.776 --> 19:09.043
No!

19:09.111 --> 19:10.611
Precious is mine!

19:31.002 --> 19:32.869
Yeah, so, that's not real fire.

19:32.937 --> 19:35.605
It's a fan blowing
luminescent plastic strips.

19:35.672 --> 19:36.973
Hey, what you guys doing?

19:38.909 --> 19:41.210
Sir, brace yourself.

19:41.277 --> 19:43.778
I have some sad and
shocking information

19:43.846 --> 19:46.047
about the 1980 men's U.
S. Hockey Team.

19:46.115 --> 19:51.385
I have discovered that one of
the players was on steroids.

19:51.453 --> 19:54.221
Which is why I've brought
this back to you.

19:54.289 --> 19:56.791
We didn't earn it and
we don't deserve it.

19:56.858 --> 19:58.326
Yeah, I'm not taking that.

19:58.393 --> 20:00.061
What? Huh? Yay!

20:00.129 --> 20:02.130
Listen, man,
we're the Winter Olympics.

20:02.198 --> 20:03.932
No one gives a crap about us.

20:04.000 --> 20:05.334
The Miracle on Ice franchise

20:05.402 --> 20:06.836
keeps the lights on in this place.

20:06.903 --> 20:10.673
But Ronald Reagan himself told
me to come here and return this.

20:10.741 --> 20:12.709
Oh, Reagan knew about the steroids.

20:12.777 --> 20:14.478
He did? Oh, yeah.

20:14.546 --> 20:17.715
But he also knew how huge
that victory was for the U.S.,

20:17.783 --> 20:20.952
so he "persuaded" us
to look the other way.

20:21.019 --> 20:23.954
That's why we have the Ron
Reagan Memorial Hot Tub.

20:24.022 --> 20:27.825
Get your asses in
this tub right now!

20:35.499 --> 20:37.234
I can't believe it.

20:37.301 --> 20:40.070
Both my heroes betrayed me.

20:40.137 --> 20:42.405
Oh, Dad, Reagan and the hockey team

20:42.473 --> 20:44.474
made mistakes just like we all do.

20:44.542 --> 20:46.877
But the good they did
still inspired you

20:46.945 --> 20:48.646
to become who you are today.

20:48.714 --> 20:50.014
It's okay to have heroes.

20:50.082 --> 20:52.450
Just don't follow and
worship them blindly.

20:52.518 --> 20:56.054
Yeah, I suppose heroes are
just normal people who...

